OL,4,C'needs significant improvement' status
OL,6,FInspectors said immediate action
OL,7,Fshould be taken in several areas
OL,8,Fincluding the checking of lifesaving
OL,9,Fequipment, the management of
OL,10,Fmedications, and the procedures in
OL,11,Fplace to conduct regular patient check-
OL,12,Fups, assessments, and observations.
OL,14,FInspectors were not assured that
OL,15,Fmedication management processes were
OL,16,Fsufficiently robust and safe due to
OL,17,Finaccuracies with administering
OL,18,Fmedication, and the inadequate
OL,19,Fmonitoring of patient conditions such
OL,20,Fas fluid intake for issuing cannulas.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G8/13
